Reasoning: 
1. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper presents a new algorithm for sampled string matching, which is a fundamental problem in computer science and involves searching for all occurrences of a pattern in a text. This falls under the scope of data structures and algorithms, making cs.DS the most likely category.
2. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) - The paper mentions applications of sampled string matching in information retrieval, which suggests that this category is also relevant.
3. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - The paper mentions natural language processing as an application of sampled string matching, which falls under the scope of computation and language.
4. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper discusses the worst-case and average-time complexity of the proposed algorithm, which is a topic within computational complexity.
5. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) - The paper involves sampling and searching for patterns in text, which can be seen as a problem in discrete mathematics.
